Case Called @ 1:08 PM: Defendant Christian James Worby in court, in custody, appearing in person.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per ADA:  Resolution recited.   Plea to Ct 1 w/o Repeater.  Probationary sentence recommended and recited.  Def confirms he agrees with State's recital.    Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea Ct 1 w/o Repeater Enh:  NC  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Outright dismissal of Repeater allegation.  No statement offered by Def.  Court accepts resolution - 90 days I/S (7 days TS credit, Huber, GT if revoked) - S/W - 1 yr probation.  Concurrent to any period of supervision or sentence.  Conditions:  15 days WCJ - commence forthwith with 7 days of TS credit; the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; No contact with Redgranite Quarry; Court Costs plus DNA surcharge - unless already done, DNA sample to be provided - sample to be provided by the end of today; Expungement of DNA record maintained by DOJ explained.  Appeal Rights Given.

Case Called @ 1:25 PM: Defendant Christian James Worby in court, appearing via video.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today - is not prepared to resolve matter today.  NGP entered by Court.  Def states he is currently on parole - asks the Court to impose Signature Bond.  States there was miscommuncation between himself and his counsel in Rock Co.  DA argues for $900 cash bond due to lack of any ties to this area and prior record.  Def makes statement as to bond request.  The Court:  Orders $900 cash bond.   STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Status conference scheduled for June 23, 2015 at 10:25 am.
